-- Sun Life Financial net profit falls 22 pct
-- By Cameron French
-- Tue May 06, 2014 05:29PM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, May 6 (Reuters) - Sun Life Financial <SLF.TO> Canada's No. 3 life insurer, said on Tuesday its first-quarter net income fell 22 percent due to the impact of last year's sale of its U.S. annuities business.

Sun life earned a net C$400 million ($367.23 million), or 65 Canadian cents in the quarter, down from a year-earlier C$513 million, or 85 Canadian cents a share.